\f0\b0 \cf0 \
The Night Hall helps to manage problem, issues between the provinces of the Outer Lands, and between the Outer Lands and other provinces, mainly the Fatunik Authority, to which all of the Outer Land theoretically pay homage, and to the Rider Council in Borded. There are occasional issues with Kahilakol and Kahilabeq as well.\
\
A main goal of the Night Hall is to provide, institutionally, for a certain degree of autonomy from the Fatunik Authority. All of the provinces of the Outer Lands maintain a mythology of origin that predates the arrival of the Fatunik and Rider Migration. They all claim to have either lived in the Saskan Lands since time immemorial, or to have arrived before the others. \
